29:06.846 --> 29:08.925
- Hello?
- AUDREY (ON PHONE): <i>Really?</i>

29:08.949 --> 29:11.928
You couldn't call me back
all day yesterday?

29:11.952 --> 29:15.097
RAMON (SIGHS): <i>Mom. I'm good.</i>

29:15.121 --> 29:17.366
I believe you, but I want to see you.

29:17.390 --> 29:19.868
<i>I'll take you to a
restaurant of your choice.</i>

29:19.892 --> 29:22.304
<i>- Tonight.</i>
- Toro Bravo. You're on.

29:22.328 --> 29:24.540
- AUDREY: <i>Oh, I love that place.</i>
- (FIRE CRACKLING)

29:24.564 --> 29:26.275
Mom, I gotta call you back.

29:26.299 --> 29:31.001
♪ ♪

29:33.004 --> 29:36.306
(WHISPERING) What the fuck are you?

29:41.012 --> 29:43.079
(BEEPING WILDLY)

29:49.882 --> 29:51.797
_

29:51.822 --> 29:55.657
♪ ♪

29:57.128 --> 29:59.128
_

30:02.433 --> 30:06.001
(CAR ALARMS BLARING OUTSIDE)

30:21.784 --> 30:23.850
♪ ♪

30:35.397 --> 30:36.707
MAN (ON PA): <i>Attention, stage.</i>

30:36.731 --> 30:38.398
<i>We're going live in 30 minutes.</i>

30:42.836 --> 30:43.813
Ooh!

30:44.364 --> 30:45.915
(CHUCKLES)

30:45.939 --> 30:47.706
Wow. Mmm.

30:51.078 --> 30:53.994
Look, I've already got several of our

30:54.019 --> 30:56.960
lawyers looking into this labor issue.

30:56.984 --> 30:59.928
It'll be resolved by the end of the day.

30:59.952 --> 31:01.964
Relax. You should have fun with this.

31:01.988 --> 31:04.055
That's not why I'm tense.

31:05.892 --> 31:07.170
My youngest son, Ramo...

31:07.194 --> 31:09.104
You know what? I don't
really wanna talk about it.

31:09.128 --> 31:12.275
Okay. Okay. Well, all you
need to do is just one thing,

31:12.299 --> 31:15.777
and then... you can take all the
time you need to deal with Ramon.

31:15.801 --> 31:17.646
- Deal with him?
- (SIGHS)

31:17.670 --> 31:21.916
Audrey, I can see
you're upset. I... (SIGHS)

31:21.940 --> 31:23.940
- Do we need to cancel?
- No.

31:25.444 --> 31:27.622
No. Of course not.

31:27.646 --> 31:29.991
Excellent. All you need
to do is keep your eye

31:30.015 --> 31:33.827
on all the good that we're gonna
accomplish with The Empathy Initiative.

31:33.851 --> 31:37.186
And I promise you that we'll
take care of this other thing.

31:38.856 --> 31:43.404
You remember Cait. She's gonna
take you back for hair and makeup

31:43.428 --> 31:45.606
and you can meet Jack and Cathy.

31:45.630 --> 31:46.674
Cait.

31:46.698 --> 31:49.564
Ms. Bayer. Please, just, uh, follow me.

31:55.606 --> 31:57.317
SHARON: Ashley!
- Hi.

31:57.341 --> 32:00.119
- Hi. Sit, please.
- Thank you.

32:00.143 --> 32:02.589
Do you want anything to eat or drink?

32:02.613 --> 32:04.379
Uh, no, no, I'm good.

32:05.215 --> 32:07.326
- (BOTH SIGH)
- You are good.

32:07.350 --> 32:08.927
(BOTH LAUGH)

32:08.951 --> 32:10.395
So, where's Cliff?

32:10.419 --> 32:12.564
Oh, Cliff is no longer with us.

32:12.588 --> 32:15.900
- We are so happy to have you here.
- Thank you.

32:15.924 --> 32:17.802
I'm so happy to have you here.

32:17.826 --> 32:20.372
I get to check off two boxes with you.

32:20.396 --> 32:22.906
(NERVOUS LAUGH) I'm sorry?

32:22.930 --> 32:26.299
Oh, I get to say that because
I'm a double-boxer myself.

32:28.035 --> 32:31.782
S... So I'm a diversity hire?

32:31.806 --> 32:36.242
Oh God, no. No. I'm just
saying it doesn't hurt, right?

32:37.412 --> 32:39.578
It looks good, it is good?

32:41.948 --> 32:45.094
Ashley, don't make this
into a thing, please.

32:45.118 --> 32:49.165
It was just a tasteless
and very... un-PC joke.

32:49.189 --> 32:51.368
- Uh...
- Apologies.

32:51.392 --> 32:54.993
You're here because of your
work and nothing else, okay?

32:56.029 --> 32:57.906
Speaking of which...

32:57.930 --> 32:59.475
I love that dress.

32:59.875 --> 33:01.343
- It's fabulous.
- Thank you.

33:01.367 --> 33:04.045
- (CLEARS THROAT)
- Yeah. Very Cloth.

33:04.069 --> 33:06.248
It sounds so simple.

33:06.272 --> 33:08.684
- (LAUGHS)
- That's exactly what I said, Jack.

33:08.708 --> 33:11.119
It is simple.
I mean, do we want to invest

33:11.143 --> 33:13.688
in teaching kids empathy skills?

33:13.712 --> 33:17.558
(ON TV) <i>We believe doing so
would profoundly affect society</i>

33:17.582 --> 33:19.894
<i>in so many positive ways.</i>

33:19.918 --> 33:21.429
CATHY: I love it.

33:21.453 --> 33:23.331
Ah. Well, if Cathy loves it...

33:23.355 --> 33:25.288
(BOTH LAUGH)

33:27.559 --> 33:30.870
Okay. We have a call from Lake Oswego.

33:30.894 --> 33:32.339
You're live on the air. What's your name?

33:32.363 --> 33:35.642
<i>Hi, I'm Bridget from the Coalition
for Humane Labor Practices.</i>

33:35.666 --> 33:37.844
Oh, we thought you were from Lake Oswego.

33:37.868 --> 33:39.479
(LAUGHS) I want to make it clear...

33:39.503 --> 33:41.515
- What's on your mind, Bridget?
- BRIDGET: <i>Yeah, I was wondering</i>

33:41.539 --> 33:45.073
<i>how The Empathy Initiative
works alongside child labor?</i>

33:46.711 --> 33:48.854
Benjamin Ventures is in the process...

33:48.878 --> 33:50.823
BRIDGET: <i>Which</i> The
Washington Post <i>now alleges,</i>

33:50.847 --> 33:54.059
<i>in addition to the worker suicides
has led to a humanitarian crisis.</i>

33:54.083 --> 33:56.929
Thank you, Bridget. Do we have
another caller on the line?

33:56.953 --> 33:59.565
Look, the child labor
allegations were news to us.

33:59.589 --> 34:01.734
<i>The minute we found out, we divested</i>

34:01.758 --> 34:04.602
from the emerging markets fund
that was in question.

34:04.626 --> 34:07.706
What I'd like to talk about
is The Empathy Initiative.

34:07.730 --> 34:10.174
Divested, huh?

34:10.197 --> 34:12.944
Just walked away? Washed your
hands of the whole thing?

34:12.967 --> 34:16.414
Well, of course. I couldn't
possibly continue to profit...

34:16.438 --> 34:19.116
So, that's what's important,
you not profiting?

34:19.139 --> 34:20.318
Of course not, but...

34:20.342 --> 34:22.118
Do you even care if it keeps happening

34:22.141 --> 34:24.588
or is it just about the optics to you?

34:24.612 --> 34:25.956
Are you suggesting that I...

34:25.980 --> 34:28.024
Do something? Yeah. You're a billionaire.

34:28.047 --> 34:29.560
- JACK: <i>Should we go to commercial?</i>
- CATHY: <i> Yeah.</i>

34:29.583 --> 34:31.527
AUDREY: <i>Don't cut me off.
I'm not done yet.</i>

34:31.552 --> 34:34.063
You know, the thing about
The Empathy Initiative is...

34:34.088 --> 34:36.356
is it's just a shiny distraction, Jack,

34:36.380 --> 34:39.524
to keep from looking too closely at
what really goes on all over the globe.

34:40.827 --> 34:41.917
It's business.

34:41.940 --> 34:43.406
(JACK AND CATHY CHUCKLE NERVOUSLY)

34:43.429 --> 34:44.774
JACK: <i>We'll be right back.</i>

34:44.797 --> 34:46.542
♪ ♪

34:46.565 --> 34:48.010
KRISTEN: Oh my God.

34:48.034 --> 34:49.478
(LAUGHS)

34:49.503 --> 34:51.714
STEVEN: <i>This is why liberals always lose.</i>

34:51.737 --> 34:54.250
Anything less than Utopian
is unacceptable.

34:54.274 --> 34:56.585
Yeah, I want everything
to be better for everybody,

34:56.609 --> 34:59.153
and I do everything I can
to make that a reality.

34:59.177 --> 35:01.823
For me, that's recycling
and driving a hybrid.

35:01.847 --> 35:03.759
For you... oh, I don't know...

35:03.783 --> 35:06.495
- not using child labor.
- I didn't know!

35:06.519 --> 35:09.097
I just found out,
and I'm trying to fix it!

35:09.121 --> 35:10.465
Spending some of your millions

35:10.489 --> 35:14.034
creating a workplace where people
don't wanna kill themselves?

35:14.058 --> 35:16.392
Do you really think
you're not complicit here?

35:17.962 --> 35:21.174
Do you know where every article
of clothing you own comes from?

35:21.198 --> 35:24.412
Everything you eat? Everything
